---
import LegalLayout from "@/layouts/LegalLayout.astro";

export const prerender = true;

const sections = [
  { id: "scope", label: "Scope" },
  { id: "prohibited", label: "What's prohibited" },
  { id: "security", label: "Security research" },
  { id: "enforcement", label: "Enforcement" },
  { id: "report", label: "Report abuse" },
];
---
<LegalLayout
  title="Acceptable Use Policy"
  description="The rules for using ZafTech products and services responsibly."
  effectiveDate="2026-04-24"
  lastUpdated="2026-04-24"
  sections={sections}
  summary="Short list, strict rules. These apply to anyone using a ZafTech product or service and form part of the Terms of Service."
>
  <h2 id="scope" data-num="01">Scope</h2>
  <p>
    This Acceptable Use Policy ("AUP") applies to everyone with access to a ZafTech
    account, website, or product (Convia, Mizan, RMS, Anchor, Talos, and future
    products). It is part of the <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a>.
  </p>

  <h2 id="prohibited" data-num="02">What's prohibited</h2>
  <p>You will not use our services to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Break any law. This includes laws of your jurisdiction, our jurisdiction, and anywhere your data travels.</li>
    <li>Harass, threaten, defame, or target anyone.</li>
    <li>Send unsolicited bulk email, SMS, or marketing without a verifiable opt-in.</li>
    <li>Distribute malware, ransomware, or phishing content.</li>
    <li>Scrape, crawl, or automatically extract content beyond rate limits we publish.</li>
    <li>Reverse engineer, decompile, or disassemble our software except where prohibition is not permitted by law.</li>
    <li>Access accounts or data that are not yours, including through credential stuffing, session hijacking, or social engineering.</li>
    <li>Probe, scan, or test the vulnerability of our systems without prior written permission (see security research below).</li>
    <li>Interfere with or degrade our services, for example by overwhelming our rate limits or uploading pathological payloads.</li>
    <li>Use our products to build, train, or power a directly competing product.</li>
    <li>Resell, sublicense, or white-label our services without a written agreement.</li>
    <li>Upload content you do not have rights to, or content that infringes trademarks, copyrights, trade secrets, or privacy.</li>
    <li>Collect special-category personal data (health, biometric, political, religious, etc.) without a lawful basis and proper notice to the people concerned.</li>
    <li>Use our products to generate or distribute child sexual abuse material, terrorism-promoting content, or content that incites violence.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="security" data-num="03">Security research</h2>
  <p>
    We welcome responsible disclosure. If you believe you have found a
    vulnerability, email <a href="mailto:contact@zaftech.co">contact@zaftech.co</a>
    (subject: "Security") with reproduction steps. Do not exploit it beyond what
    is needed to confirm the issue, do not access data that is not yours, and give
    us a reasonable window to fix it before public disclosure. In return we will
    acknowledge you and keep you updated.
  </p>

  <h2 id="enforcement" data-num="04">Enforcement</h2>
  <p>
    If we reasonably believe you have violated this AUP we may, without prior
    notice: (a) remove the offending content, (b) suspend or terminate your
    account, (c) deny refunds for affected periods, and (d) report the matter to
    law enforcement. For severe violations (for example, CSAM, active attacks, or
    fraud) we will act immediately and without warning.
  </p>

  <h2 id="report" data-num="05">Report abuse</h2>
  <p>
    Seeing something that looks like a violation? Email
    <a href="mailto:contact@zaftech.co">contact@zaftech.co</a> with the URL, the
    account or content in question, and a short description. Serious reports are
    reviewed within one business day.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
